If the expenditure is so great, the ambassador has at least managed the aliair successfully in reseuing the merchandise from the enemy. The verselets of Martial apply here: “The judge makes application and so does the advocate; my view, Sextus, is that you should pay your creditor.” For there are two species of gain from an enemy; the one complete, when we disadvantage him and advan- tage ourselves; the other half-complete, when we only disadvantage him. Let this owner of the eight chests seek an account of those expenses from his Lordship, the ambassador, and he shall receive it when there is need, when the other owners of the remaining chests are present.
